Individual-society-culture. Semiotics and contemporary social theories. Divergence of social theories. Main trends in social theories and semiotics. Microinteractionism and semiotics. Individual-culture-society: Semiotic Self. Semiotics and social theories: principles of transdisciplinary analysis.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Origins of several societal and culture theories in semiotics are introduced. Connections between pragmaticism and semiotics are viewed, and the societal nature of semiotics as a discipline will be shown there through.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  A student accomplished the course will be able to see semiotics as a social science, and the genuine and original semiotic nature of social sciences. Students will apprehend the interrelated nature of semiotics and societal and culture studies. S/he will obtain contemporary image of the development of disciplines into inter- and transdisciplinarity.
